**Located behind the {{ill|Autumn Shrine|ja|秋宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Autumn Shrine|qq=}} of Suwa Taisha Shimosha. Dedicated to {{ill|Ebisu|ja|えびす|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebisu|qq=}}.

* {{ill|Hiruko Shrine|ja|蛭子社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hiruko Shrine|qq=}} (Takei Ebisu) (Suwa City)

**One of the subordinate shrines of Suwa Taisha Kamisha. Includes the ruins of Takei Hata and Takei Castle.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Takei Hata Ruins|url=https://suwacitymuseum.jp/nandemo/koumoku/0100/010212.htm}}</ref>

* {{ill|Ōtomo Shrine (Saku)|ja|大伴神社 (佐久市望月)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtomo Shrine (Saku)|qq=}} (Saku City, Mochizuki)

**Traditionally linked to Takei Ōtomonushi, though evidence is speculative.<ref>‘Saku County Gazetteer,’ 1983.</ref>
